values:
National Frost

If you missed National Frost last time, I would advise you all not to miss them again. These Ex-Filmmaker members are currently headlining a show at the SLED ISLAND festival in Calgary, playing alongside the likes of Les Savy Fav, Spoon, The Boredoms, and Julie Doiron and are at no pace to stop now. I'm almost positive these guys will be opening for high profile bands like the Arcade Fire, Stars, or Black Mountain. I wouldn't want to miss this show.

Monday, JULY 2 The Lamplighter w/ Bel Riose, Alphababy 9PM / $7

 

Geronimo (Ex-Despistado)


Formerly Despistado, a great band that was lucky enough to sign to the illustrious Jade Tree Records, have reformed to create Geronimo, starting right where Despistado left off. If Despistado was any indication of how successful these guys were, I would see no reason why these Cap'n Jazz/Joan of Arc offspring couldn't get right back to where they were twice as fast.

Thursday, JULY 5 The Lamplighter w/ Catlow, Shukov 9PM / $7

 


 

The Noble Firs


Although the Noble Firs are not as well known as they should be, it would be wrong to dismiss them as local upstarts. These guys are close to being veterans in the music scene, performing on stages, touring, and putting out records as the ACCIDENT since late 99'. It doesn't sound like that long, but the shelf life of some bands these days are way too short. The Noble Firs mix a Silver Jews sort of warmth to a rootsy style indie rock.

Friday, JULY 6 The Lamplighter w/ The Whisky Jacks, Earls Town Winter, Vale 9PM / $10

 


 

Scatterheart


This will be a spectacle to see as it always is when Scatterheart takes the stage. It's hard to pinpoint Scatterheart as sounding like one genre of music. They easily blend glam rock and classic rock with Brit-rock and the Cure. Along with them are numerous guests including the Belladonnas, Bradley, and Girls on Top Burlesque!

Saturday, JULY 7 The Lamplighter: The Elastic Cabaret w/ The Bella Donnas, Bradley, Girls on Top BurlesqueThe Whisky Jacks, Earls Town Winter, Vale 8PM / $10

Crayonsmith is from Dublin Ireland and is making a stop at the Lamplighter tonight. He is currently on tour with Casiotone for the Painfully Alone and has toured with the likes of Sparklehorse, Scout Nibblett, and more! Nire is joining them from Portland as well as Old Bridge from Vancouver and The Poison Dart. Check them all out - Nire is so amazing. i love them. CRAYONSMITH http://www.myspace.com/crayonsmith NIRE http://www.myspace.com/niremusic OLD BRIDGE http://www.myspace.com/hussainraving $6 / 9pm
